hands_on_practices.solution:
1. Governing 1D isentropic Euler system  
$$\rho_t +(\rho u)_x=0,\quad (\rho u)_t+(\rho u^2+p)_x=0,\quad p=p(\rho)\,. $$  
Along $dx/dt=u+c$ the invariant satisfies  
$$dR_+=du+\frac{dp}{\rho\,c}=0\;\Longrightarrow\;R_+=u+\int\frac{dp}{\rho\,c}\,. $$

2. For a perfect gas mixture with constant mass fractions $x_i$, molar masses $M_i$ and heat ratios $\gamma_i$, define  
$$M^{-1}=\frac{x_1}{M_1}+\frac{x_2}{M_2},\quad c^2=\gamma_{\rm mix}\,\frac{p}{\rho},$$  
$$c_{v,\,{\rm mix}}=\!R_u\Bigl(\frac{x_1}{M_1(\gamma_1-1)}+\frac{x_2}{M_2(\gamma_2-1)}\Bigr),\;
R_{\rm mix}=\!R_u\,M^{-1},\;
\gamma_{\rm mix}=1+\frac{R_{\rm mix}}{c_{v,\,{\rm mix}}}\,. $$

3. Isentropic law $p=K\rho^{\gamma_{\rm mix}}$ gives  
$$dp=c^2\,d\rho,\quad\int\frac{dp}{\rho\,c}
=\int\frac{c^2\,d\rho}{\rho\,c}
=\int\frac{c\,d\rho}{\rho}=\frac{2c}{\gamma_{\rm mix}-1}\,. $$

4. Substitute $\displaystyle\gamma_{\rm mix}-1
=\frac{M^{-1}}{R_u^{-1}c_{v,{\rm mix}}}
=\frac{\frac{x_1}{M_1}+\frac{x_2}{M_2}}
{\frac{x_1}{M_1(\gamma_1-1)}+\frac{x_2}{M_2(\gamma_2-1)}}$  
to obtain  
$$R_+=u+\frac{2c}{\gamma_{\rm mix}-1}
=u+\frac{2c\bigl(\frac{x_1}{M_1(\gamma_1-1)}+\frac{x_2}{M_2(\gamma_2-1)}\bigr)}
{\frac{x_1}{M_1}+\frac{x_2}{M_2}}\,. $$
